Implements an AVLNode which keeps the offset updated.

This node contains the real work. TreeList is just there to implement java.util.List. The nodes don't know the index of the object they are holding. They do know however their position relative to their parent node. This allows to calculate the index of a node while traversing the tree.
The Faedelung calculation stores a flag for both the left and right child to indicate if they are a child (false) or a link as in linked list (true).
